      "Jesus went to the tomb. He wept. He asked that the stone covering the entrance be removed. Martha cautioned about the odour given the time elapsed. The stone was removed. Jesus called out in a loud voice: Lazarus, come out.",
      "The dead man came out. His hands and feet were still bound with burial strips and a cloth covered his face. Jesus told the people nearby to unwrap him and let him go. Many who witnessed the event placed their faith in Jesus. Others left immediately to report it to the chief priests in Jerusalem.",
