      `The angel of God and the pillar of cloud moved from in front of the Israelites and stood behind them between the two camps, bringing darkness to one side and light to the other. Moses stretched out his hand over the sea. Throughout the night the LORD drove the sea back with a strong east wind, turning it into dry land. The Israelites went through the sea on dry ground with a wall of water on their right and on their left.`,
      `The Egyptians pursued them into the sea. The LORD threw the Egyptian army into confusion, jamming the wheels of their chariots. The Egyptians said: let us flee — the LORD is fighting for them against Egypt.`
