      `For the burnt offering: the fire on the altar was to be kept burning throughout the night, and the priest was to get up early each morning, dress in his linen garments and undergarments, remove the ashes from the altar, carry them outside the camp to a clean place. Then he was to stoke the fire with fresh wood and arrange the burnt offering on it. The fire was to be kept burning continuously — it was never to go out.`,
      `For the grain offering: Aaron and his sons were to bring it to the altar and burn a handful as a memorial portion. The rest they could eat, without yeast, in the courtyard of the tent of meeting. It was not to be baked with yeast. It was most holy. The anointed priest was to prepare the daily grain offering — half in the morning and half in the evening — entirely burned, not eaten.`
