      `If the Israelites followed God's decrees and kept his commands: rain would come in its season, the ground would yield its crops, the trees would yield their fruit, threshing would continue until grape harvest and grape harvest until planting. They would eat all the food they wanted and live in safety. God would grant peace. They would lie down with no one to make them afraid. He would walk among them and be their God. He had broken the bars of their yoke and brought them out with heads held high.`,
      `But if they did not listen: terror, wasting disease, and fever would destroy their sight and drain their life. Their enemies would eat what they sowed. They would plant their seeds in vain because their enemies would eat the harvest. God would set his face against them so they would be defeated by their enemies.`,
      `If after all this they still did not listen, punishment would be multiplied seven times over — wild animals attacking their children and livestock, roads becoming deserted. If they still did not pay attention and walked in hostility toward God, he would walk in hostility toward them and punish them seven times for their sins. The cities would become ruins, the sanctuaries desolate. God would scatter them among the nations.`,
      `Yet if they confessed their sins and the sins of their ancestors, and if their uncircumcised hearts were humbled, God would remember his covenant with Jacob, Isaac, and Abraham. He would remember the land. He had not rejected them or abhorred them to destroy them completely. He was the LORD their God. These were the decrees, laws, and regulations given through Moses on Mount Sinai.`
