      `They stood before Moses, Eleazar the priest, the leaders, and the whole assembly at the entrance to the tent of meeting and said: our father died in the wilderness. He had no sons. Why should our father's name disappear from his clan because he had no son? Give us property among our father's relatives.`,
      `Moses brought their case before the LORD. The LORD said to Moses: what Zelophehad's daughters are saying is right. You must certainly give them property as an inheritance among their father's relatives and give their father's inheritance to them.`,
      `The LORD also established a general order of inheritance: to a man's sons first; if no sons then daughters; if no daughters then brothers; if no brothers then the father's brothers; if no father's brothers then the nearest relative.`,
      `The LORD then told Moses to go up into the mountains to view the land — he would see it but would not enter it, because he had rebelled against the LORD's command at the waters of Meribah. Moses asked the LORD to appoint a new leader for the community. The LORD told him to take Joshua son of Nun, a man in whom the Spirit dwells, and commission him. Moses did so before Eleazar and the whole assembly.`
