      `Moses and the elders commanded the people: when you have crossed the Jordan into the land the LORD is giving you, set up large stones, coat them with plaster, and write on them all the words of this law. On Mount Ebal build an altar of uncut stones — do not use any iron tool on them — and offer burnt offerings and fellowship offerings. Eat there and rejoice before the LORD.`,
      `Six tribes were to stand on Mount Gerizim to bless the people: Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Joseph, and Benjamin. Six were to stand on Mount Ebal to pronounce curses: Reuben, Gad, Asher, Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali.`,
      `The Levites were to recite twelve curses in a loud voice — for making idols, for dishonoring parents, for moving a neighbor's boundary stone, for leading the blind astray, for withholding justice from the foreigner and fatherless and widow, for killing an innocent person in secret, for accepting a bribe to kill an innocent person. And after each one, all the people were to say: Amen.`
