      `Joshua set an ambush behind the city. He took thirty thousand fighting men and sent them out at night, instructing them: you are to ambush the city from behind. I and all those with me will advance on the city, and when the men come out against us, we will flee from them as before. They will pursue us until we have lured them away from the city, for they will say the Israelites are running from us as before.`,
      `When the men of Ai looked behind them, they saw smoke rising against the sky and had no chance to escape in any direction, for the Israelites who had been fleeing toward the wilderness had turned back against their pursuers. The men of the ambush quickly captured the city and set it on fire. The city was burned and its ruins became a desolate heap to this day.`,
      `Joshua built an altar on Mount Ebal and made burnt offerings and fellowship offerings. There, in the presence of the Israelites, Joshua wrote on stones a copy of the law of Moses. All Israel — with their elders, officials, and judges — stood on both sides of the ark, before the Levitical priests. Joshua read all the words of the law, the blessings and curses, according to all that was written in the Book of the Law.`
