      `They answered: your servants have come from a very distant country because of the fame of the LORD your God. We have heard reports of him — all that he did in Egypt and all he did to Sihon and Og. Our elders and all those living in our country said to us: take provisions for your journey; go and meet them and say we are your servants. This bread was warm when we packed it at home, but now it is dry and moldy. These wineskins were new, but see how cracked they are.`,
      `The Israelites sampled their provisions but did not inquire of the LORD. Then Joshua made a treaty of peace with them. Three days after the treaty was made, the Israelites heard that they were neighbors — they lived near them. The whole assembly grumbled against the leaders, but the leaders answered: we have given them our oath by the LORD, the God of Israel, and we cannot touch them. Joshua made the Gibeonites woodcutters and water carriers for the assembly and for the altar of the LORD.`
