      `He urged them to be very strong and to keep and to do everything written in the Book of the Law of Moses, without turning aside to the right or to the left. He warned them not to associate with the nations that remained among them, not to invoke the names of their gods or swear by them, and not to serve them or bow down to them. They were to hold fast to the LORD as they had done to this day.`,
      `But Joshua issued a solemn warning: if you turn away and ally yourselves with the survivors of these nations that remain among you and if you intermarry with them and associate with them, then you may be sure that the LORD your God will no longer drive out these nations before you. Instead, they will become snares and traps for you, whips on your backs and thorns in your eyes, until you perish from this good land.`
