      `The Ephraimites were angry with Gideon: why didn't you call us when you went to fight Midian? They argued with him sharply. He calmed them: what have I accomplished compared to you? God gave Oreb and Zeeb, the Midianite leaders, into your hands. Their anger subsided.`,
      `Gideon and his three hundred men crossed the Jordan, exhausted yet still pursuing. He asked the men of Succoth for bread for his troops who were weary. The officials of Succoth said: why should we give bread to your troops? Do you already have Zebah and Zalmunna in your hand? Gideon replied: when the LORD has given them into my hand, I will tear your flesh with desert thorns and briers. The same happened at Peniel — they gave him the same answer, and he said: when I return in triumph I will pull down this tower.`,
      `Gideon captured the two Midianite kings, Zebah and Zalmunna, and routed their forces. He returned and punished the men of Succoth as promised, and pulled down the tower of Peniel. He asked the two kings about the men they had killed at Tabor. They answered: men like you, each one with the bearing of a prince. These were my brothers, Gideon said, the sons of my own mother. He told his firstborn son Jether to strike them down, but the boy was afraid. Gideon himself stepped forward and killed them.`
