      `Abimelek son of Jerub-Baal went to his mother's brothers in Shechem and said to them: which is better for you — to have all seventy of Jerub-Baal's sons rule over you, or just one man? Remember, I am your flesh and blood. His mother's brothers repeated these words to all the citizens of Shechem, and they were inclined to follow Abimelek, for they said: he is our brother. They gave him seventy shekels of silver from the temple of Baal-Berith, and Abimelek used it to hire reckless scoundrels, who became his followers.`,
      `He went to his father's home at Ophrah and on one stone murdered his seventy brothers, the sons of Jerub-Baal. But Jotham, the youngest son of Jerub-Baal, escaped by hiding. Then all the citizens of Shechem and Beth Millo crowned Abimelek king.`,
      `When Jotham was told, he climbed to the top of Mount Gerizim and shouted down to them the parable of the trees seeking a king. The trees asked the olive tree to be their king — it refused. They asked the fig tree — it refused. They asked the vine — it refused. Finally they said to the thornbush: come and be our king. The thornbush said: if you really want to anoint me king, come and take refuge in my shade. But if not, let fire come out of the thornbush and consume the cedars of Lebanon.`,
      `Jotham cried: have you acted honorably and in good faith toward Jerub-Baal and his family? Then may Abimelek be your joy, and may you be his. But if you have not, let fire come out from Abimelek and consume you, citizens of Shechem and Beth Millo, and let fire come out from you and consume Abimelek.`
