    summary: `After Abimelek had governed Israel three years, God stirred up animosity between him and the citizens of Shechem, who acted treacherously against him. This happened so that the crime against Jerub-Baal's seventy sons would be avenged. The citizens of Shechem set men on the hillto`,
    ref: "Judges 9:22–57",
    anchorVerse: null,
