      `Samson went to Gaza and spent the night with a prostitute. The men of Gaza surrounded the place and lay in wait for him all night. But Samson lay there only until the middle of the night. Then he got up, grabbed the doors of the city gate — posts and all — lifted them off, put them on his shoulders, and carried them to the top of the hill facing Hebron.`,
      `Some time later he fell in love with a woman in the Valley of Sorek named Delilah. The rulers of the Philistines went to her and said: see if you can lure him into showing you the secret of his great strength. Each of us will give you eleven hundred shekels of silver.`,
      `Delilah said to Samson: tell me the secret of your great strength and how you can be tied up and subdued. Samson answered: if anyone ties me with seven fresh bowstrings that have not been dried, I'll become as weak as any other man. She had men hidden in the room. She bound him with the seven bowstrings. She called out: Samson, the Philistines are upon you. He snapped the bowstrings as easily as a piece of string snaps when it comes close to fire.`,
      `She bound him with new ropes. He snapped them. Then she wove his seven braids into the fabric and tightened it with a pin. Same result. Each time, the Philistines were waiting in the room. Each time, Samson snapped free.`
