      `The five men went to Laish, where they found a peaceful and unsuspecting people, living in safety, lacking nothing, prosperous, and far from the Sidonians with no relationship with anyone else. They returned and convinced the tribe to march. Six hundred armed Danites set out. They came to Micah's house, took the idol, the ephod, the household gods, and the image. The priest asked: what are you doing? They told him to keep quiet and come with them — be a father and priest to a whole tribe rather than to one man's household. The priest was glad. He took the ephod, the household gods, and the image.`,
      `When Micah and his neighbors caught up, the Danites said: don't argue or some of us will attack you. Micah saw he was outmatched and turned around and went home. The Danites then went to Laish, attacked its peaceful and unsuspecting people, put them to the sword, and burned down their city. There was no one to rescue them because they lived far from Sidon. They rebuilt the city and settled there. They set up the idol Micah had made for themselves, and it remained there as long as the house of God was in Shiloh.`
