      `After four years Absalom asked David if he could go to Hebron to fulfill a vow. The king told him to go in peace. But Absalom had sent secret messengers throughout the tribes of Israel: as soon as you hear the sound of the trumpets, say Absalom is king in Hebron. Two hundred men from Jerusalem had accompanied him, invited guests who went quite innocently, knowing nothing about the matter.`,
      `A messenger came and told David: the hearts of Israel are with Absalom. David said to all his officials who were with him in Jerusalem: come, we must flee. Hurry or Absalom will overtake us. David fled on foot, weeping as he went, his head covered and his feet bare. All the people with him covered their heads and were weeping as they fled. Then someone told David: Ahithophel is among the conspirators with Absalom. David prayed: LORD, turn Ahithophel's counsel into foolishness.`
