      `Joram allied with Jehoshaphat king of Judah and the king of Edom. They marched around the Desert of Edom for seven days but ran out of water for the army and their animals. Jehoshaphat asked for a prophet of the LORD. Elisha was found. He said to Joram: I would not even look at you if it were not for Jehoshaphat. Then he called for a harpist. As the harpist played, the hand of the LORD came on Elisha. He said: this is what the LORD says — I will fill this valley with pools of water. You will not see wind or rain, yet this valley will be filled with water. He also said the LORD would deliver Moab into their hands.`,
      `In the morning the valley was filled with water flowing from Edom. When the Moabites saw the water, it looked red like blood. They said: those kings must have fought and killed each other. To the plunder, Moab. But when they came to the camp, the Israelites rose and fought them, slaughtering them and marching on into Moab, destroying towns, stopping up springs, and felling trees.`,
      `When the king of Moab saw the battle had gone against him, he took his firstborn son and sacrificed him as a burnt offering on the city wall. The fury against Israel was great and they withdrew.`
